\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. J. sabina} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 1039 (1753). Dioecious shrub, usually low and spreading. Twigs 0·6-0·8 mm wide, quadrangular. Leaves strongly foetid, all decussate; adult leaves 1-1·25 mm, ovate appressed, obtuse to subacute, with an elliptical gland on the back entire, the border not scarious. Female cone 4-6 mm, ripening in the autumn of the first year or in the following spring, usually depressed-globose, bluish-black, pruinose; stalk short, recurved scaly. Seeds usually 2, free. 2n = 22. •{\i  Mountains of S. & C. Europe; also at low altitudes in S.E. Russia.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs It Ju Po Rm Rs(C, W, K, E).
