\pard\f0\fs28 Twigs irregularly alternate. Male flowers solitary, each consisting of 6-14 peltate anthers with 4-8 pollen-sacs. Female flower consisting of several imbricate scales, the uppermost fertile. Seeds ovoid, partly surrounded by a fleshy, usually scarlet, aril, ripening the first year.
